                                                                                                archived for long-term storage (e.g., because of legal requirements or to decrypt archived
                                                                                                data). A key-recovery capability is needed whenever keys are backed up or archived. This
                                                                                                capability needs to be designed so that the keys can be recovered in an acceptable amount
                                                                                                of time and only by those entities authorized to do so; see SP 800-57, Part 1 for more
                                                                                                information about key backup, key archiving, and the recovery of backed up and archived
                                                                                                keys.
